1 department, pursuant to legislative appropriations, for providing grants in accordance
2 with this section to rural communities in the state to support, create, or improve local
3 housing, workforce, business recruitment and commerce, infrastructure, or other
4 community needs. Funding may not be provided for operating funds of a local entity.
5 4. The commissioner shall appoint a rural community endowment fund committee
6 consisting of the commissioner, nine individuals residing in rural communities, and a
7 representative of a nonprofit organization dedicated to supporting housing initiatives,
8 social and cultural events, and small businesses in rural communities of the state. Of
9 the nine individuals residing in rural communities, five individuals must be appointed
10 for a term of two years and four individuals must be appointed for an initial term of
11 one year. Thereafter, the four individuals must be appointed for two - year terms. Terms
12 shall commence on September first of the year of appointment. The commissioner
13 shall serve as the chairman of the committee.
14 5. The rural community endowment fund committee shall award grants from the rural
15 community endowment fund. When awarding grants from the fund, the committee
16 shall prioritize projects that support the long - term prosperity, independence, safety ,
17 health, and quality of life of rural communities and their citizens. The committee shall
18 determine funding application and evaluation processes, including grant award
19 amounts and recipients, priority of projects, and evaluation criteria of approved
20 projects.
21 6. The department shall contract with a nonprofit organization dedicated to supporting
22 housing initiatives, social and cultural events, and small businesses in rural
23 communities in the state to assist the department in administering the rural community
24 endowment fund and provide recommendations to the rural community endowment
25 fund committee related to funding, awards, projects, and other purposes. The
26 department may expend up to ten percent of funding available for distribution in the
27 rural community endowment fund for costs of administering the program.
28 7. For purposes of this section, "rural community" means a city with a population of fewer
29 than one thousand individuals as determined by the most recent decennial census .
30 8. Before July first of each year, the department shall report to the legislative
31 management regarding the status of the rural community endowment fund, use of
